					<B>What is life like at the sanctuary?</B><br>
					
					Rabbits at the sanctuary are able to live naturally in family groups. They do not have to dodge cars, or run from coyotes, or dodge hawks and owls. They are well fed and happy and have a much longer average life than they did on their own outside of the sanctuary. 
					
