					<p align=center><font face="arial" size="4"><b>Great Rabbit Migration to Rabbit Meadows!</b></font><br><p align=left><img src="onebunny.jpg" align="right" hspace="5"><font face="arial" size="3">  Hundreds of rabbits from the Best Friends "Great Rabbit Rescue" will shortly be arriving at our sanctuary.  <p>On, Best Friends Animal Sanctuary in Utah agreed to take on the rescue of over a thousand rabbits discovered living in horrible conditions in one back yard in Reno Nevada.  The rescue effort was huge, involving hundreds of volunteers and a staggering amount of effort and money.  The rabbits were relocated temporarily to a rented ranch outside of Reno, where they were spayed, neutered and treated for numerous medical problems.  Despite the rescue workers'  24/7 effort, rabbit numbers swelled to 1600 as pregnant rabbits delivered their babies daily while waiting for their turn at the spay table. <p><img src="mainrescue.jpg" align="left">While the babies will most likely be social and adoptable since they are used to contact with the volunteers, many of the older rabbits are feral and afraid of people.  They need a  place where they can live out their lives in more natural, but safe, conditions.  Providing this environment is what we at Rabbit Meadows do best!

We are excited to welcome these new residents, who deserve a chance at spending their remaining years free from fear, pain and hunger.  Check back for pictures and updates of their arrival and adjustment.


